oseo.com/how-to-add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website/\">How to Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Website</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27334:\"<p>Do you want to know how to add Google Search Console to your WordPress website? One of the most important steps in optimizing your WordPress site for SEO is adding it to Google Search Console.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know that the average person searches for something online <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-statistics/\" title=\"81 SEO Statistics for 2024 (Current &amp; Verified)\">3-4 times a day</a>? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s, therefore, important to make sure Google sees your website and shows it in search results. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is the first step to driving traffic to your site, boosting conversions, and growing your business. After all, if Google doesn’t know your site exists, no one else will either.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we’ll show you how to add Google Search Console to your WordPress website so that you can monitor your site’s presence in Google search results and improve your SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please feel free to use these quick links to jump straight to the sections you want:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#what-is-google-search-console\">What Is Google Search Console?</a></li><li><a href=\"#add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website\">Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Website</a></li><li><a href=\"#easily-verify-your-wordpress-site-using-asioseo\">Easily Connect Your WordPress Site Using AIOSEO</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-1-install-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">Step 1: Install All In One SEO (AIOSEO)</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-why-use-aioseo-to-verify-your-site-with-google-search-console\">Why Use AIOSEO to Verify Your Site with Google Search Console?</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-3-access-aioseos-webmaster-tools\">Step 2: Access AIOSEO&#x2019;s Webmaster Tools</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-4-connect-to-google-search-console-no-verification-code-required\">Step 4: Connect to Google Search Console [No Verification Code Required]</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website\">How to Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Website: Your FAQs Answered</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-google-search-console\">What is Google Search Console?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-why-should-i-add-my-wordpress-site-to-google-search-console\">Why should I add my WordPress site to Google Search Console?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-can-i-add-google-search-console-through-my-wordpress-dashboard\">Can I add Google Search Console through my WordPress dashboard?</a></li></ul></li></ul></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s start by explaining Google Search Console and why it&#8217;s a helpful tool for website owners.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"what-is-google-search-console\"><strong>What Is Google Search Console?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-search-console-homepage.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"614\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-search-console-homepage.png\" alt=\"How to Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Website\" class=\"wp-image-25056\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-search-console-homepage.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-search-console-homepage-300x252.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/google-search-console-homepage-600x505.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Google Search Console, formerly known as “Google Webmaster Tools,” is a free service available to all website owners.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It shows you how Google indexes and adds your website to search results, so you can ensure that the right people are seeing your site. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With Google Search Console, you can:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Confirm that Google can locate and crawl your WordPress site</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Submit new content for <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/indexing-in-seo/\" title=\"What Is Indexing in SEO? A Beginner’s Guide [Plus Tips]\">indexing</a> and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Create a Sitemap in WordPress (The Easy Way)\">add a sitemap</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Analyze your site&#8217;s impressions, clicks, and position on Google</li>\n\n\n\n<li>See which search queries (search terms) cause your site to appear in search results</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Delete or <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-hide-a-wordpress-page-from-google/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">hide content from Google</a> so it doesn’t appear in search results</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Find and fix common malware and spam issues</li>\n\n\n\n<li>See which other sites are linking to your site</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Test if your <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/mobile-seo/\" title=\"Mobile SEO: How to Optimize Your Site for Mobile Devices\">mobile site</a> is driving traffic to your site</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>In other words, Google Search Console is a helpful tool that gives you information about your site and the people visiting it. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>That being the case, let’s take a look at how to add Google Search Console to your WordPress website.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website\">Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Website</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-google-search-console-to-wordpress.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"344\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-google-search-console-to-wordpress.png\" alt=\"Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Site\" class=\"wp-image-24893\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-google-search-console-to-wordpress.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-google-search-console-to-wordpress-300x141.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-google-search-console-to-wordpress-600x283.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, head over to <a href=\"https://search.google.com/search-console/about\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google Search Console</a> and click on the <strong>Start Now</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, sign in with your Google / Gmail account.&nbsp;If you don’t have one yet, you can create an account <a href=\"https://support.google.com/mail/answer/56256?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s easy and will only take you a couple of minutes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve created your Google / Gmail account and logged in, you’ll see a welcome page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/welcome-screen-in-google-search-console.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"596\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/welcome-screen-in-google-search-console.png\" alt=\"Welcome to Google Search Console page\" class=\"wp-image-24894\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/welcome-screen-in-google-search-console.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/welcome-screen-in-google-search-console-300x245.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/welcome-screen-in-google-search-console-600x490.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On the right side of the page, you’ll see a box called <strong>URL prefix</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on this box, enter the full URL for your website, and then click the <strong>Continue </strong>button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-url-prefix-to-google-search-console.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"706\" height=\"620\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-url-prefix-to-google-search-console.png\" alt=\"How to add Google Search Console to your WordPress website - enter URL prefix\" class=\"wp-image-24895\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-url-prefix-to-google-search-console.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-url-prefix-to-google-search-console-300x263.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/add-url-prefix-to-google-search-console-600x527.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>The URL you enter must exactly match the URL for your site. This includes https://&nbsp;and www, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After you&#8217;ve clicked continue, it will take you to a new <strong>Verify ownership</strong> window. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’re going to use the HTML tag to verify your WordPress website with Google.&nbsp;With that said, simply scroll down to <strong>Other verification</strong> methods, and click on the <strong>HTML tag </strong>option.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-search-console.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"716\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-search-console.png\" alt=\"How to add Google Search Console to your WordPress website - HTML tag\" class=\"wp-image-24896\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-search-console.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-search-console-300x294.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/verify-website-ownership-in-google-search-console-600x588.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will open a new window with the meta tag that you need to add to your WordPress site’s homepage.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/copy-html-tag-in-google-search-console.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"523\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/copy-html-tag-in-google-search-console.png\" alt=\"How to add Google Search Console to your WordPress website - copy HTML tag\" class=\"wp-image-24897\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/copy-html-tag-in-google-search-console.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/copy-html-tag-in-google-search-console-300x215.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/copy-html-tag-in-google-search-console-600x430.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you need to click on the<strong> Copy</strong> button to copy the HTML tag.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Anyway, you can now open a new browser window and log into your WordPress site.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the next step, we&#8217;re going to show you how to easily verify your WordPress site with Google Search Console using the best SEO plugin in the market, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"easily-verify-your-wordpress-site-using-asioseo\">Easily Connect Your WordPress Site Using AIOSEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Many people find the above method complicated and tedious. That&#8217;s why we decided to create a flow that&#8217;s super easy—you don&#8217;t even need to use a verification code.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-step-1-install-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">Step 1: Install All In One SEO (AIOSEO)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step to connecting your site to Google Search Console is to install a powerful SEO plugin like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"All in One SEO - WordPress SEO Plugin and Toolkit\">All In One SEO</a> (AIOSEO).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO can help you connect your site without the Google Search Console verification code.\" class=\"wp-image-151544\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"All in One SEO - WordPress SEO Plugin and Toolkit\">AIOSEO</a> is the best WordPress SEO plugin on the market. Over 3 million savvy website owners and marketers trust it to help them dominate the SERPs (<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-are-serps/\" title=\"What Are SERPs (And Why Are they Important to SEO)?\">search engine results pages</a>) and drive relevant site traffic.&nbsp;This is because of the powerful <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/\" title=\"Features\">SEO features and modules</a> designed to help 