author-seo-google-e-e-a-t/\" title=\"Author SEO – Google E-E-A-T Addon\">Author SEO</a>, and many more.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Automatic syncing of sitemaps: When you verify your site with AIOSEO, your sitemaps automatically sync with GSC. This results in faster indexing and an advantage in ranking higher on SERPs.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>It&#8217;s much easier</strong>: AIOSEO takes the grunt work out of so many SEO tasks, including verifying your site with GSC. You don&#8217;t have to know coding, and most features are enabled by default, so you only have to install the plugin, and it&#8217;s all set!</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know why you should use AIOSEO, let&#8217;s take a look at how to easily verify your site with Google Search Console.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-step-3-access-aioseos-webmaster-tools\">Step 2: Access AIOSEO’s Webmaster Tools</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO installed and an active Google account, you can now move to the next step in connecting your site to GSC—the easy way. To do that, head to AIOSEO’s <strong>Webmaster Tools</strong> section. If your site is not yet connected to GSC, you’ll get a prompt asking if you have:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1000\" height=\"323\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/google-search-console-verification-question.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO\'s Webmaster tools prompt for GSC connection.\" class=\"wp-image-321080\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/google-search-console-verification-question.png 1000w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/google-search-console-verification-question-300x97.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/google-search-console-verification-question-768x248.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/google-search-console-verification-question-600x194.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can click the <strong>Connect to Google Search Console</strong> or the <strong>Google</strong> icon if you’re not connected.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1000\" height=\"396\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/webmaster-tools-gsc.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO\'s Webmaster Tools.\" class=\"wp-image-321081\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/webmaster-tools-gsc.png 1000w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/webmaster-tools-gsc-300x119.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/webmaster-tools-gsc-768x304.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/webmaster-tools-gsc-600x238.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-step-4-connect-to-google-search-console-no-verification-code-required\">Step 4: Connect to Google Search Console [No Verification Code Required]</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When you click the <strong>Connect to Google Search Console</strong> or the <strong>Google</strong> links, you trigger a flow for connecting to GSC.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"902\" height=\"545\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-1.png\" alt=\"Getting started setting up GSC without a Google Search Console verification code.\" class=\"wp-image-321082\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-1.png 902w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-1-300x181.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-1-768x464.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-1-600x363.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the <strong>Connect to Google Search Console</strong> button to start the connection wizard. The first step requires you to select the Google account you want to use to connect to GSC.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1002\" height=\"538\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-account-selection.png\" alt=\"Choosing the Google account to use when setting up GSC\" class=\"wp-image-321086\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-account-selection.png 1002w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-account-selection-300x161.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-account-selection-768x412.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-account-selection-600x322.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you’ll be asked to sign in to your AIOSEO account:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1000\" height=\"383\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-2.png\" alt=\"Prompt to sign in to AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-321089\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-2.png 1000w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-2-300x115.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-2-768x294.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-2-600x230.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you sign in by clicking <strong>Continue</strong>, you&#8217;ll be asked to give AIOSEO permission to access your GSC account.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1002\" height=\"548\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-permissions.png\" alt=\"Permissions for AIOSEO to access your GSC account.\" class=\"wp-image-321090\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-permissions.png 1002w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-permissions-300x164.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-permissions-768x420.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-permissions-600x328.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you click <strong>Allow,</strong> you will be taken to the last step, where you verify site ownership by clicking a button:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"477\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-complete-setup.png\" alt=\"Confirming AIOSEO/GSC connection.\" class=\"wp-image-321094\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-complete-setup.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-complete-setup-300x204.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-complete-setup-600x408.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you click <strong>Complete Connection</strong>, your site will be connected to GSC. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"902\" height=\"558\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-success.png\" alt=\"Succesful GSC connection.\" class=\"wp-image-321095\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-success.png 902w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-success-300x186.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-success-768x475.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/gsc-flow-success-600x371.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve connected your site to Google Search Console—and that without using a Google Search Console verification code!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And there you have it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve now successfully added Google Search Console to your WordPress website. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-how-to-add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website\">How to Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Website: Your FAQs Answered</h2>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-what-is-google-search-console\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">What is Google Search Console?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>Google Search Console (formerly Google Webmaster Tools) is a free service provided by Google that allows website owners to monitor their site&#8217;s performance in Google search results. It provides data on search traffic, crawl errors, search analytics, and more.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-why-should-i-add-my-wordpress-site-to-google-search-console\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">Why should I add my WordPress site to Google Search Console?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>Adding your site gives you access to valuable data about how Google crawls and indexes your pages. This lets you monitor for any issues and optimize your site&#8217;s visibility in search results. It also allows you to submit sitemaps to help Google discover your content.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-can-i-add-google-search-console-through-my-wordpress-dashboard\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">Can I add Google Search Console through my WordPress dashboard?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>Yes. With an SEO plugin like AIOSEO, adding GSC through your WordPress dashboard is super easy. With AIOSEO, you don&#8217;t even have to go through the hoops of copying and pasting verification codes or HTML tags.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this post helped you know how to add Google Search Console to your WordPress site. You may also want to check out other articles on our blog, like our tutorial on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-html-sitemap-to-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Add an HTML Sitemap to Your WordPress Website\">adding an HTML sitemap</a> in WordPress or our guide to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/index-your-website-on-google/\" title=\"10 Quick &amp; Easy Ways to Index Your Website on Google\">improving your indexing</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">X (Twitter)</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>\n</div></div>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website/\">How to Add Google Search Console to Your WordPress Website</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-google-search-console-to-your-wordpress-website/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2:\"12\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"How to Optimize a Site Built with the Thrive Architect Page Builder [Using the AIOSEO Integration]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\